<subSubSection pageId="708" pageNumber="709" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph pageId="708" pageNumber="709">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="708" pageNumber="709">
Noonan (1991: 211) treated this taxon as a group within the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="708" pageNumber="709" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="708" pageNumber="709">Harpalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Lindroth (1968: 748), Kryzhanovskij et al. (1995: 140), and Kataev et al. (2003: 370) regarded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tschitscherine" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalobrachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="708" pageNumber="709" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="708" pageNumber="709">Harpalobrachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
